    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Sanford</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 167.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 8, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 20th of March, No. 250, has
                    just been received. The subject to which it relates is an important one, and the
                    suggestions you have <pb facs="0160" n="78" xml:id="pg_78"/> offered are
                    valuable. I have submitted the despatch for perusal to the Secretary of the
                    Treasury.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., Brussels.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
